<HEADLINE> China, Germany Top Groups to Make Last Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANCHESTER, England, April 26 (Xinhua) -- China and Germany
clinched their fifth straight wins in the group competition on
Thursday, both moving into the women's team quarter-finals at the
World Table Tennis Championships.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion China beat Belgium 3-0 to top Group A and
Germany nipped Chinese Taipei 3-1 to emerge winner in Group C.
</P>
<P>
South Korea and Romania have also booked the quarter-final
spots.
</P>
<P>
Chinese youngsters Li Ju, Wang Nan and Wang Chen, ranked fifth,
seventh and ninth in the world, completed China's 3-0 victory.
</P>
<P>
Unlike China which only lost a game in five matches, European
champion Germany won the group in a difficult fashion, with three
matches fought to five games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
