<HEADLINE> Villeneuve, Frentzen Given Suspended One-race Bans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Jacques Villeneuve and
German Heinz-Harald Frentzen were each given suspended one-race
bans Saturday after dominating qualifying race for Sunday's San
Marino Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
The sanction against the Williams-Renault pair was for "not
having slowed down sufficiently" on seeing waved yellow flags
indicating a dangerous situation such as a car having just
crashed, said the International Automobile Federation (FIA).
</P>
<P>
The ban will be applied if they offend in either of the next
two races, in Imola, Italy and in Monaco.
</P>
<P>
Italian Nicola Larini was also fined 5,000 dollars for
exceeding the pits speed limit in his Sauber Petronas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
