<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Beats Norway in World Championships Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Canada crushed Norway 7-0 to win
its opening match at the World Ice Hockey Championship in Turku,
Finland, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Canadians blasted two goals within 39 seconds halfway into
the first period and cruised home over the hapless Norwegians.
</P>
<P>
Bob Errey tapped in the rebound after a shot by Dean Evason
10:18 into the game to open the scoring for Canada.
</P>
<P>
Geoff Sanderson got the first of his two goals 39 second later
by firing a slap shot from near the blue line low to the glove
side of Norway's goalkeeper Robert Norman Schistad.
</P>
<P>
Sanderson got his second at 14:16 by deflecting into the net a
shot by Don Sweeny.
</P>
<P>
After surviving a two-man disadvantage for 1:31 minutes early
in the second period, Canada struck again as soon as it was back
at full strength. had an assist in the goal by Owen Nolan 3:05
into the period.
</P>
<P>
Keith Primeau and Anson Carter followed with goals spaced 48
seconds apart for a 6-0 Canadian lead 4:59 into the middle period.
</P>
<P>
Rob Zamuner came from behind the net to flick in Canada's
seventh at 13:46. 
</P>
</TEXT>
