<HEADLINE> Singapore Prime Minister to Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong will pay a working visit to China from Sunday, the Prime
Minister's Office said today in a statement.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, Goh is scheduled to meet Chinese President Jiang
Zemin, Premier Li Peng, Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference Chairman Li Ruihuan and Vice Premier Li Lanqing.
</P>
<P>
Goh will also visit Dalian in Liaoning Province, and Nanjing
and Suzhou in Jiangsu Province, before departing from China's
largest city of Shanghai on May 3 to Hong Kong, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
He will be accompanied by Minister for Trade and Industry Lee
Yock Suan, Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Ow Chin Hock, and
a group of Singapore businessmen.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister visited China in May 1995. 
</P>
