<HEADLINE> Ericsson, of Sweden, Reports Improved Earnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 26 (Xinhua)-- Swedish telecommunications giant
Ericsson reported first-quarter pre-tax earnings up 30 percent, at
2 billion Swedish kronor (about 260 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
For the 22nd consecutive quarter, Ericsson received increased
orders worth 39.2 billion kronor (4 billion dollars) during the
first three months of the year, said a report available today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the group's sales surged 36 percent to 30.7 billion
kronor (3.1 billion dollars), with the nearly 100 percent rises
coming from its mobile phone and computer terminal operations.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Officer Lars Ramqvist attributed the high
performance to the group's solid market organization and hefty
investment in research and development activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
