<HEADLINE> Former Presidential Chief of Staff Yegorov Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Former presidential chief of staff
Nikolai Yegorov died of illness in Moscow on Friday, the Itar-Tass
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yegorov, 46, served as presidential chief of staff between
January and July 1996. After that he became the governor of the
Krasnodar region, southern Russia, but soon failed in
gubernatorial elections in December.
</P>
<P>
He also worked as Russian minister for nationalities and
regional affairs in May 1994, and from December 1994 to June 1995,
he was vice-prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Yegorov will be buried on April 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
