<HEADLINE> ECO News Agencies Explore Cooperation in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Ten news agencies of the member
countries of the Economic Cooperation Organization (ECO) started
here today its first conference on regional cooperation
in the field of information and trade.
</P>
<P>
The ECO groups together Iran, Turkey, Pakistan, Kazakhstan,
Tajikistan, Afghanistan, Uzbekistan, Kyrghizistan, Turkmenistan and
Azerbaijan.
</P>
<P>
Fereydoun Verdinejad, Managing Director of the Islamic Republic
News Agency (IRNA) inaugurated the session and underlined the
need for expansion of regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that speedy circulation of information, especially in
the areas of economy and trade, would serve as a factor
for expansion of cooperation among the countries concerned.
</P>
<P>
ECO Secretary General Oundar Ouza called for an expansion of
cooperation among the member countries in information
dissemination.
</P>
<P>
Ekrem Kara Ismail Oglu, Managing Director of Turkey's Anatolian
News Agencies, said that facilitating the exchange of information
was a need felt by all members, therefore, efforts should be
made in that concern.
</P>
<P>
The managing directors of ECO news agencies are to exchange
views on the article of association concerning setting up a pool
and on the quality of mutual cooperation at the two-day
meeting.
</P>
<P>
They are also to explore ways and means of establishing
an economic data dissemination network and of upgrading
cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
