<HEADLINE> ``People's Daily'' Urges Staff-Cut Efficiency Move </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- In a commentator's article to be
released tomorrow, the ``People's Daily'' suggests that state
enterprises could improve their efficiency by cutting the number
of their employees.
</P>
<P>
Overstaffing is a common problem faced by state-owned firms in
China, but Yanzhou Coal Mining areas, now known as the "Yanzhou
Ming (Group) Company Ltd", has succeeded in increasing its
efficiency fourfold by cutting back on the number of miners it
employs and adopting advanced technology and equipment, the paper
says.
</P>
<P>
The article praises the Yanzhou Coal Mining Administration for
its success and terms its policy the right road for other
state-owned firms to follow when carrying out reform and
development.
</P>
<P>
Only by implementing this principle can state-owned firms
increase their efficiency and obtain better economic performances,
and it is a basic task for the deepening of enterprise reform, the
paper says.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, according to the article, the most important task
for state-owned firms wishing to improve their efficiency is to
bring about scientific and technological progress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
