<HEADLINE> De La Rosa Wins Opener of Formula Nippon Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Pedro De La Rosa, driving a
Lola T97-51, burst ahead after 19 laps and won the opener of the
10-race 1997 Formula Nippon Japanese auto racing championship in
Suzuka on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard clocked a winning time of one hour three minutes
and 21.391 seconds to complete the 35 laps around the 5.864-km
Suzuka Circuit in central Japan.
</P>
<P>
De La Rosa set an average speed of 194.36-km an hour.
</P>
<P>
Takuya Kurosawa of Japan, driving a Lola T96-52, was second in
1:03:27.366, followed by Hidetoshi Mitsusada of Japan in
1:03:30.837 and Tetsu Motoyama of Japan in 1:03:44.660.
</P>
<P>
Sarah Kavanagh of Ireland, the first woman driver ever to
compete in this series, finished 14th in 1:05:00.624 for 32 laps
among 26 starting cars. 
</P>
