<HEADLINE> Guangxi Economy Does Well in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region generated 38.2 billion yuan in gross domestic
product (GDP) in the first three months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The figure represents a rise of 8.3 percent over the same
period of last year, sources at the region's statistics bureau
said.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural situation, in particular, has been
encouraging, as the regional government has attached more
importance to agriculture, resulting in a bumper harvest for early
rice and marked rises in the production of animal husbandry and
aquatic products.
</P>
<P>
Industrial added value in the first quarter of the year stood
at 12.7 billion yuan, an increase of 7.1 percent, while the ratio
of production of manufactured goods against marketing was 85
percent, a growth of three percentage points. Exports of
locally-made commodities surged by 25.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The region has invested 2.6 billion yuan in fixed assets in the
past three months, up 11.8 percent over the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The region also recorded 15.8 billion yuan in retail sales of
consumer commodities in the first three months of this year, a
rise of 10.7 percent over the same period of last year, and
achieved 458 million US dollars-worth of imports and exports, up
4.6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
