<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Singaporean Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) met with Singaporean Prime Minister Goh Chok
Tong here today.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in the Great Hall of the People, Li said
that, as friendly neighbors, China and Singapore have maintained a
steady exchange of visits and contacts between their leaders and
kept extending bilateral cooperation and exchanges in the fields
of economy, science, technology and culture since they forged
diplomatic ties. China is satisfied with the smooth growth of
bilateral relations, he added.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have great potential for friendly
cooperation, based on the high degree of complementarity of the
two economies, Li noted, adding that Singapore has the advantage
in skills, capital and management expertise, while China boasts
abundant natural and human resources, and a huge market.
</P>
<P>
It is worth learning from Singapore how it preserves and
promotes traditional Oriental culture in the process of absorbing
the advanced achievements of other countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Li said, China needs internal conditions of unity and
stability, as well as a peaceful and friendly international
environment for its economic development.
</P>
<P>
He went on to note that China pursues an independent foreign
policy of peace and seeks to maintain peace in the Asia-Pacific
region and in the world at large. It is ready to develop friendly
relations with its neighbors, including Singapore, and all other
nations, he said. This is in the fundamental interests of China
and is certainly not an expedient measure.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong said his visit to China is aimed
at further strengthening relations between the two countries and
exchanging views with Chinese leaders on issues of common
concern. He said he hoped that the visit would further boost
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The two sides conferred on regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Goh arrived here this afternoon for a working visit to China at
the invitation of Chinese Premier Li Peng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
