<HEADLINE> 5 Turkish Soldiers Killed in Operations Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Five soldiers of the Turkish
security forces were killed in recent operations against the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in southeastern Turkey, an
official statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the Turkish security forces had wiped out 19 PKK
rebels in the same operations in the region.
</P>
<P>
It added that the Turkish government troops shot dead 14 PKK
militants in Caci mountains near Eruh town of Siirt province,
three in Bongol province and two in the Derecik area of Semdinli
town of Hakkari province linking northern Iraq and Iran.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Turkish reliable sources told Xinhua that dozens
of Turkish armored vehicles had crossed into northern Iraq in
preparation for launching military operations in the region
where most PKK rebels are based.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that there are better weather conditions in
the region for the Turkish government troops to strike at the
PKK.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan has said that his
government would spare no efforts to eliminate the PKK
guerrillas by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Over 21,000 people including civilians, PKK rebels and
government troops have been killed in conflicts since August
1984 when the PKK started separatist war in southeastern Turkey
for autonomy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
