<HEADLINE> Dhaka Makes Bid for Becoming Neat, Clean City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
initiated certain steps to ease traffic jam in the crowded capital
city of Dhaka as well as to free it from waterlogging and garbage,
official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
To present the residents with a neat and clean capital city,
the concerned authority has fixed a deadline and sought
cooperation from all sections of people and relevant agencies to
make the bid a success.
</P>
<P>
May 15 is the deadline set by a high-powered coordination
committee meeting recently, which urged the government and private
organizations, hospitals, business establishments and house-owners
to clean their respective premises.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also called upon all to clean ponds, drains and
marshy lands, to remove construction materials from the city roads
and to keep the footpaths free for movement of pedestrians.
</P>
<P>
Several decisions were also taken for reducing traffic jam and
removing waterlogging in this city with a population of over 8
million.
</P>
<P>
The decisions include programs to increase public awareness
about traffic rules, intensifying the construction works of
underpass and box culverts, to construct more overbridges and link
roads on both sides of the railroad passing through Dhaka city.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Dhaka City Corporation will continue its program
throughout the year to kill mosquito larvae in ponds, drains and
other water bodies and marshes so that spread of mosquitoes could
be controlled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
