Liberal Party enjoy a commanding lead over other parties --
anywhere from 22 to 40 percent points ahead of its nearest
competitor the Progressive Conservatives.
</P>
<P>
That would ordinarily all but guarantee a second, easy majority
victory for the ruling Liberals, analysts here said.
</P>
<P>
The Liberal won a landslide victory in the 1993 federal
election, scooping 177 seats in the then 295-member House of
Commons. 
