<HEADLINE> Mount Emei Receives Over 20 Million Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Mount Emei, a scenic spot in
southwest China's Sichuan Province, has received more than 20
million tourists from 70 countries and regions since it opened to
the public 1979.
</P>
<P>
The mountain receives some one million tourists a year, and the
tourism zone has over 400 hotels and restaurants, with four
two-star hotels and 10,000 beds. Available for visitors are 200
tour buses, two travel agencies and two cableways.
</P>
<P>
Mount Emei is renowned for its Buddhist temples as well as its
superb scenery.  
</P>
