<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Enterprises Booming in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Foreign-backed enterprises are
contributing heavily to the economy of this north China port city,
as they accounted for 41 percent of its industrial production in
the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Their total sales were worth 18.6 billion yuan in the first
quarter, up more than 30 percent over the same period of last
year, according to the city's statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
Overseas enterprises produced 1.8 billion yuan in profits and
taxes in the first quarter, nearly a 25 percent increase, and 700
million US dollars-worth of exports, up 41 percent. Their profits
and taxes in the first two months made up as much as 73 percent of
the city's total.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has maintained a double-digit increase in using
overseas investment over the past four years. It now has more
than 10,000 foreign-funded enterprises, with a total investment of
16 billion US dollars, two-thirds of which are employed in the
industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, joint ventures in Tianjin employ 320,000 people,
playing an important role in easing the city's employment pressure.
</P>
</TEXT>
