<HEADLINE> International Agricultural Exchanges Active in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
attracted 213 agricultural experts and scholars from seven
countries, including the US, Canada and Japan, last year.
</P>
<P>
In 1995 alone, 65 foreign agricultural experts visited the
province, which neighbors China's capital of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Such foreign expertise has advanced the local ability to handle
biological disease prevention and treatment, irrigation, fruit
growing and botanical research, and improved the province's
agricultural research level, according to provincial officials.
</P>
<P>
