<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egyptian Teachers Attacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Unidentified gunmen have
attacked and opened fire on a mini-bus transporting Egyptian
teachers and local staff members in north Mogadishu this morning.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place near Rowda mosque of Shibbis district
where the Egyptians live and they were heading to the school of
Majma Umul Qura of north Mogadishu where they teach.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitness accounts, the gunmen about five armed
with assault rifles were driving a taxi and opened fire as they
came round the corner on the bus carrying about seven Egyptian
teachers and two security guards and a driver. The incident which
seemed to have been precalculated has left the two security
guards and the driver get seriously wounded following the return
of fire by the security guards.
</P>
<P>
With little hope, the two security men and the driver were
rushed to Keysaney hospital for treatment. Also one of the
Egyptian teachers has suffered slight shrapnel injuries on his
right arm during the exchange of fire. The gunmen have escaped
unhurt after the neighbors of the area have come out to help.
</P>
<P>
The shocked Egyptian teachers have come out of the vehicle
bewildered. However, the man who sustained the slight injury on
his right arm using a lemon to stop the bleeding said they will
not be discouraged by the incident and therefore will further
continue their job which he characterized as holy effort.
</P>
<P>
According to the eyewitness, the perpetrators who probably
aimed at hijacking the mini-bus have managed to confiscate the
two guns used by the body guards of the Egyptian teachers, but
failed to take away the vehicle itself. There has been no
official word from the local authority of Shibbis district yet,
however a number of armed militiamen from the Islamic court were
seen patrolling the area in an attempt to locate the culprits.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian teachers teach at the only elementary and
intermediat e school where few thousand students from both sides
of the capital attend. The school, Majma Umul Qura is funded by
the government of Saudi Arabia. However the students pay each 1.5
to 3 US dollars per month which is used for the sanitation and
watchmen of the school.
</P>
<P>
A similar school is being run by Egyptian teachers in the
central town of Beletuein where more than 5000 students attend
their intermediate classes. One more school is also being taught
by the Egyptians in Qardo district of northeastern region
controlled by the SSDF faction. Since the collapse of the former
regime, the regular system of education has also collapsed, but
still some elementary and intermediate schools are being run by
Muslim and Arab agencies country wide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
