<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PICC Life Boosts Sales Through Individual Agents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- PICC Life, a subsidiary of
China's biggest insurer, the People's Insurance Company of
China (PICC), expects a sharp growth of sales by its 80,000
individual agents this year -- topping five billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
PICC Life is now the country's largest life insurance
company. It was reshaped into a limited-liability company from a
former life insurance department of the PICC last year. The
company now has a team of almost 80,000 individual sales agents,
40,000 regular employees and about 3,000 branches nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yaohua, vice-president of PICC Life, said the company is
expected to overtake the Ping An Insurance Co. Ltd in sales by
individual agents within this year. Ping An has led home insurers
in this aspect.
</P>
<P>
Ping An, headquartered in Shenzhen, was the first Chinese
insurer to introduce the individual sales agent system to boost
its urban sales.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of this year the total sales of PICC life
reached 7.8 billion yuan-worth, an increase of 107 percent over
the figure for the same period of last year, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the company's total spending on business expansion
has been slashed by two percentage points, Wang noted.
</P>
<P>
According to the company's statistics, PICC life had a total of
300 million insurance policies that were still valid at the end of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Insurance specialists say that the rapid growth of China's
economy and that of the annual income of Chinese residents will
expand the insurance market.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the total premium income in China's life
insurance business will reach around 120 billion yuan by the end of
this century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
