<HEADLINE> Hepatitis B, Top Killer of Nigerian Males </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Hepatitis B infections which
attack human liver cells have become the biggiest single killer
of Nigerian males between the ages of 20 and 40, according to the
medical experts.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian medical experts at a recent symposium on liver cancer
and hepatitis virus also agreed that Nigeria has one of the
highest rates of infection of the disease worldwide with about 90
percent children in contact with the virus by the age of 17.
</P>
<P>
Hepatitis B infection is now the ninth highest cause of death
around the world, the Sunday Vanguard reported today.
</P>
<P>
The participants also urged the government to act fast to
arrest the situation so as to safeguard the present and future
health of the Nigerian populace.  
</P>
