<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan's Foreign Exchange Reserve Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The foreign exchange reserve of
Kazakhstan has dropped 3.6 billion tenge (47.5 million U.S.
dollars), or 3.6 percent, to 98.4 billion tenge (1.3 billion
dollars) over the first four months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Alievich Djandosov, president of the central bank of
Kazakhstan, attributed the fall mainly to the devaluation of gold
in the world market.
</P>
<P>
The slide of the gold price has caused a loss of 2 billion
tenge (27.2 million dollars) to Kazakhstan's foreign exchange
reserve, said Djandosov.
</P>
<P>
The president said the country's main tasks for this year, set
in the 1996-1998 economic program, will be to curb inflation and
stablize the value of tenge. 
