<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Financial Sector Stable In 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The first three months of this
year witnessed a stable and healthy movement of the stock, foreign
exchange and capital markets here in Shanghai, China's largest
metropolis and financial center.
</P>
<P>
The securities market had further expanded in the quarter, with
the total turnover climbing to 804.9 billion yuan, six times the
figure for the same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
The turnover of stock was 321.8 billion yuan, nearly 11 times
that in the same 1996 period, while the transaction of state bonds
topped 459.5 billion yuan, six times that for the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
On the last trading day of the first quarter, the SSE Composite
Index went up to 1,234 points, up over 300 points compared with
the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The China Foreign Exchange Trading Center, located in the city,
operated smoothly in the first three months, with little
fluctuation regarding the exchange rates between Chinese currency
and the convertibles.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the center traded 13.4 billion US dollars,
7.75 billion HK dollars and 22.09 billion yen, which totaled 14.58
billion US dollars while counting all tradings by US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's capital market was quite brisk during the first
three months as the National Inter-Bank Loan Market, which is also
situated in the city, transacted 143.5 billion yuan, including
68.1 billion yuan in the primary market and 75.4 billion yuan in
the secondary market.
</P>
<P>
During the period, Shanghai remained to be a main capital
supply area to other parts of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
