<HEADLINE> SADC Urged To Enhance Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The South Africa
Development Community (SADC) member states have been urged to
enhance regional integration and exploit fully the economic
potentials of the region.
</P>
<P>
Several SADC ambassadors in a goodwill mission to Tanzania and
Uganda made this appeal here over the weekend, saying that
economic regional integration would enable the member states
enjoy the advantages of the economies of scale and compete well
in international markets.
</P>
<P>
"In economic terms, this region could play a great role and
become one of the economic tigers like countries of South East
Asia", stressed Tanzania's Ambassador to South Africa, Mr. Ammy
Mpungwe.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Mpungwe told the SADC ambassadors' dialogue on
regional co-operation in the field of transportation held at the
Dar es Salaam Sheratonn Hotel that regional integration would
also enable the region complete effectively under the trade
liberalization.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhille, a lecturer of the University of Dar es Salaam, Dr.
Mohabe Nyirabu said at the meeting that the issue of regional
integration was no longer a choice, except to pursue it
vigorously.
</P>
<P>
Nyirabu said that regional integration would also reduce
operational costs, remove trade barriers and promote business in
the region.
</P>
<P>
He added that the partner states need to design comprehensive
schemes suitable in hastening the regional integration growth.
</P>
<P>
He also appealed to the states to sacrifice and transfer some
of the powers in favour of the regional integration and formulate
policies likely to promote the regional relations.
</P>
<P>
Other countries represented at the dialogue included Zimbabwe,
Namibia, Uganda, Malawi, Mauritius and Mozambique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
