<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Company Develops New Tomato Seeds Extractor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 27 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli company has
developed a new tomato seeds extractor the TS-1000, it was learned
from the Israel Export Institute.
</P>
<P>
In a traditional way, fermentation tanks are used to strip
tomato seeds of their membranes before drying. It not only
takes up space, but uses approximately 10 cubic meters of
water per one kilogram of clean seeds for the cleansing process.
</P>
<P>
The new machine, TS-1000, developed by a Kiryat Weizmann Science
Park incubator company Inter-Nevet Ltd. (U.S. patent pending) use
only 2 cubic meters of water and instead of 1-2 days, purifies
tomatoes almost instantly at rates of two to three kilograms of
seeds per hour.
</P>
<P>
Weighing 200 kilograms, the TS-1000 is easily transportable, so
tomatoes can be processed in the fields.
</P>
<P>
The seed extraction process is also highly controllable,
allowing factors such as temperature, humidity and speed to be
adjusted.
</P>
<P>
A protype has already been developed and tested, and
further tests are under way. In tests by Israel's largest seed
producer Hazera, the TS-1000 seeds proved high germination rates
compared to seeds produced through standard fermentation methods.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
