<HEADLINE> Kuwait Starts Navy Exercises with Allies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait started a three-day
joint naval exercises with the U.S., British and French warships
today in a bid to coordinate team work against any possible threat.
</P>
<P>
The war games code-named "Eager Sentry" is being participated
by the Kuwaiti warship Al-Sanbouk, USS Ingram, USS Ardent, the
British missile destroyer HMS Southampton and French frigate
George Legues.
</P>
<P>
The main goal of the exercise was to "advance relationships
and increase the interoperability of the Western Navies with
the Gulf state by exercising in an environment of all the
threats we can possibly think off," Southanmpton commanding
officer Duncan Potts said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The ships participating in the exercises will sail off in
a simulated mine field transit, and during the three days at
sea, the ships will do anti-surface ship exercises with
Kuwaiti naval patrol boats simulating the opposition.
</P>
<P>
Air defense and live surface firing in an area just off
Kuwait will also be conducted during the exercises course.
</P>
<P>
This is the first that a multi-national wargames is being
held in the Gulf since the start of this year.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and its western allies held dozens of various kinds
of military exercises since the Gulf War within the framework
of military cooperation agreements signed with them.
</P>
<P>
This exercise came at the heels of a recent Iranian war games
in the Gulf in which Iran reportedly deployed more than 200,000
troops and conducted air, land and sea exercises as well as
missile firing exercises.
</P>
<P>
In two weeks, the U.S. and British warships will be
exercising with Bahraini naval forces to be followed by
training with the navy of Saudi Arabia, sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
