<HEADLINE> Chang Faces Stafford in US Clay Court Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Michael Chang
rallied to beat Australian Jason Stoltenberg for a final berth in
the US Men's Clay Court Championships in Florida on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
With a win of 4-6, 6-3, 6-3, Chang will face South African
Grant Stafford in the final, who downed sixth-seeded American
Chris Woodruff 6-3, 4-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Chang had a slow start against Stoltenberg. After taking a 2-0
lead, the American twice lost his serve as Stoltenberg rolled to a
5-4 lead and held his serve to take the first set.
</P>
<P>
Stoltenberg, two years senior than Chang, broke Chang in the
third game for a 3-1 lead in the second set before Chang completed
a sweep of the succeeding five games.
</P>
<P>
In the decider, Chang sailed further with ease with his
trademark of baseline strokes.
</P>
<P>
The win was Chang's 20th in his last 21 matches and brought his
record for the year to 27-3.
</P>
<P>
Against Stafford he'll be trying for an ATP Tour-leading fourth
title of the year and the 30th tournament victory of his career.
