<P>
In a bid to join the WTO, Russia must discuss with other
countries the adjustment of tariffs and economic regulation, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some other countries' experiences showed that
political factors could be used for preventing a country from
entering the WTO, he added.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, Russia began to apply for the membership of the
General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT), the predecessor of
the WTO. Negotiations have entered a substantially critical stage
this year.
</P>
<P>
Chubais said that in the process of the negotiations, Russia
must maintain the current scale of its foreign trade and not lose
"a single rouble or U.S. dollar."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Russia does not want to see the negotiations
dragging on for seven or eight years, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
