<HEADLINE> Morocco Closes Towards World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Morocco scored a 1-0 victory over
Sierra Leone in Freetown on Saturday, moving closer towards a
berth in the 1998 World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The sole goal was netted by Bassir Salaheddine in the 40th
minute after taking advantage of a midfield blunder of Sierra
Leone defender Mohammed Kanu.
</P>
<P>
The win put Morocco (2-1-0) three points ahead of Sierra Leone
(1-1-2) with a game in hand in Africa's Group 5.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Morocco was still awaiting a FIFA review of its
April 6 match against Gabon in Libreville, which Morocco led 4-0
before it was abandoned in the 55th minute due to fan riots.
</P>
<P>
If FIFA allows the result to stand, Morocco would move six
points of Sierra Leone with only two matches remaining.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leone's chances for an equaliser was ruled out in the
77th minute when its keeper Brima Attouga Kamara was fished out of
the pitch for an intentional handball outside the penalty area.
</P>
