<HEADLINE> Rocchigiani Retains WBO Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- German Ralf Rocchigiani retained
his World Boxing Organisation (WBO) cruiserweight title in Zurich
on Saturday, beating Swiss challenger Stefan Angehrn on points.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Rocchigiani became the first German fighter to retain a
title abroad since Max Schmelling in the 1930's.
</P>
<P>
The 34-year-old German boxer, who won his 41st out of 54 bouts
including 17 knockouts, was ruled the winner by two of the three
judges over the 32-year-old Swiss boxer who lost to the German in
December.
</P>
<P>
Rocchigiani remained unbeaten since May 1994, and was due to
make his next defence against British boxer Carl Thompson, whom he
dethroned in Manchester in June 1995. 
</P>
