<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The recent New Zealand-Zhejiang
Trade and Investment Seminar held in Hangzhou could mean increased
cooperation between New Zealand and Zhejiang, an east China
coastal province.
</P>
<P>
Economic growth in both has provided good opportunities for
trade and investment, and cooperation will be further promoted
through the efforts from governments and merchants, according to
Chris Elder, New Zealand's Ambassador to China, and Long Anding,
the province's Deputy-governor.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was sponsored by New Zealand's Consulate General in
Shanghai, and attracted 135 officials and merchants from the two
sides to discuss trade and investment prospects and to increase
understanding and trust by doing more trade and investment.
</P>
