<DOCNO> XIE19970427.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Farmers Enjoy Good Health Care </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in east China's Jiangsu
Province enjoy the best health conditions among Chinese farmers, with
an average life expectancy of 71 years, double the figure soon
after the founding of new China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
Other major health indices for the farmers in the province,
including the death rate of women in childbirth, infant mortality,
the incidence rate of the epidemic diseases, and the planned
vaccination of children, are all among the best in the country.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the health department of the province attributed
this to improved health care in recent years.
</P>
<P>
In 1987, the province began to set up a network of basic rural
health care. Some 47 counties in the province, about three
quarters of the total, have reached the standard of basic health
care by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
About 30 million farmers in 23,000 administrative villages, or
57 percent of the province's total number of farmers, have
received better medical treatment through the co-operative
medicare system.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, over ten counties or cities at county level,
introduced a medical insurance system, which can help farmers
avoid impovrishment from massive medical expenses.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, among the 870,000 people in Tongshan County, who have
joined the co-operative medicare system, 60 percent have part of
their medical expenses paid under the co-operative system. And 36
people have submitted 5,000 to 10,000 yuan of medical expenses,
and 16 people submitted more than 10,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Health care networks at the county, township, and village
levels are responsible for the prevention and treatment of common
diseases. Most of the farmers in the province's 35,000
administrative villages can see the doctor at clinics, built in
their own villages.
</P>
<P>
Many medical organizations established health records for the
farmers, and launched systematic management of the health care for
pregnant women, children, and for the anti-epidemic diseases
work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970427.0116 </DOCNO>
