<HEADLINE> Nearly 1,000 Foreign Firms in Operation in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Foreign companies and branches,
which are running different businesses in Myanmar, totaled 940 at
the end of January this year, according to the latest issue of
"The Trade News" published by the Ministry of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
The number of joint ventures between Myanmar companies
(including state-owned and private ones) and foreign enterprises
reached 103.
</P>
<P>
Under Myanmar's Foreign Investment Law enacted in November
1988, foreign companies are allowed to incorporate in the country
to do business on a wholly-owned basis or set up joint ventures
with state enterprises, cooperatives or local private companies.
</P>
<P>
Up to the end of March this year, total foreign investment in
Myanmar, which comes from 21 countries and regions, amounted to
6.05 billion U.S. dollars in 247 projects with Britain leading,
followed by Singapore, Thailand, the United States, France and
Malaysia, according to the latest official statistics.  
</P>
