<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Environmental Research Center Opens in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A center for environmental
research in humid soils was inaugurated in Cano Negro, a Costa
Rican town on the border with Nicaragua, the Environment and
Energy Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
The center "Friends of Earth" inaugurated Friday was built to
support regional sustainable development for Costa Rican and
Nicaraguan communities, said the Ministry in a communique.
</P>
<P>
The humid soils are a kind of ecological systems of a very high
biological value.
</P>
<P>
The scientists investigate the use and reproduction of
different species of animals and plants to apply them to
productive project to promote sustainable use of the resources of
the area.
</P>
<P>
This center is the first in Central America of its kind and
represents an important instrument of regional research. 
</P>
</TEXT>
