<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Competent Officials Up, Incompetent Officials Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A group of 25 incompetent
officials in Tianjin, a major port city in north China, recently
were dismissed from their posts, and 40 competent officials were
promoted, local official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The 25 dismissed officials were working in the city's posts and
telecommunications departments and pharmaceutical firms, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
A local micro switchgear plant used to be a money-losing
factory. Four years ago, the workers' representatives congress
chosed Xu Baozhong, an ordinary worker, as the head. The factory
today not only made profits but also annexed another enterprise.
</P>
<P>
"After ordinary workers gave assessment to their heads, they
realized they are the masters of the enterprises, and their sense
of responsibility was enhanced," said Jin Sheng, chairman of the
trade union of the Lisheng pharmaceutical Plant.
</P>
<P>
"In past, I did little to my company, and the assessment given
by workers was fair to me," said Liu Wulin, one of those who have
been dismissed from their original posts.
</P>
<P>
Incomplete statistics showed that nearly 60 percent of local
state-owned enterprises had carried out the assessment of their
officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
