<DOCNO> XIE19970427.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African Women Committee on Peace to Be Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 26 (xinhua) -- The 18th meeting of the
African Regional Coordination Committee for the Integration of
Women in Development (ARCC) today decided to create the African
Women Committee on Peace.
</P>
<P>
A resolution adopted at the end of the three-day meeting noted
the escalating state of conflict in several African states that
have been the root cause of sufferings in the continent.
</P>
<P>
The resolution requested that the United Nations Economic
Commission for Africa (ECA) Conference of Ministers of Economic
and Social Planning approve the creation of the African Women
Committee on Peace which will work closely with the Central Organ
of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) Mechanism for Conflict
Prevention, Management and Resolution in an advisory capacity in
matters related to the peace process.
</P>
<P>
It appealed to the OAU secretary general to accelerate the
nomination process by member states and non-governmental
organizations for the committee.
</P>
<P>
It also requested that ECA collaborate with OAU in providing a
joint secretariat to the women's committee until such time that
the committee is able to establish its own secretariat.
</P>
<P>
It further requested the ECA Conference of Ministers of
Economic and Social Planning to submit this resolution to the OAU
Council of Ministers and the African Heads of State at the
forthcoming summit for endorsement.
</P>
<P>
According to the meeting, the African Women Committee on Peace
will be autonomous in nature, comprising 16 countries from the
five OAU sub-regions.
</P>
<P>
It will consist of six government officials, five members from
non-governmental organizations and five members nominated in
their personal capacity.
</P>
<P>
Governments representatives will serve for a year while the
rest will serve for two years for continuity. All members will
selected from the countries that constitute the OAU central
organ.
</P>
<P>
Another resolution adopted at the meeting is "Resolution on
the Structure, Role and Functions of the African Regional
Coordinating Committee for the Integration of Women in
Development."
</P>
<P>
ARCC was established in 1979 by the ECA Conference of
Ministers. It is an inter-governmental policy-making body that
focuses on the advancement of women.
</P>
<P>
It is the political arm of the ECA's gender program, which is
implemented by the African Center for Women. ARCC meets annually
to review the work of the center, and to provide it with
orientation and guidance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970427.0139 </DOCNO>
