<HEADLINE> Yemeni Vice President Meets Somali Faction Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni Vice President Abdo Rabo
Mansour Hadi met here today with a visiting Somali delegation
headed by Hussein Farah Eideed, leader of Somalia's National
Alliance.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Hadi and Eideed discussed the developments
in Somali and the attitudes of the political forces and factions
there, the Yemeni News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides expressed their eagerness for restoring stability
and security in Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The Yemeni vice president pointed out that the parties involved
in the conflict in Somali should be brought together in Sanaa to
bring their views closer.
</P>
<P>
He added that Yemen, together with all those who are interested
in security and unity of Somali, are ready to do all they can to
get Somali out of its ordeal.
</P>
<P>
The Somali delegation arrived in Sanaa Friday for a visit of
several days to Yemen. 
</P>
