<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen Passes Away(2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Comrade Peng Zhen's life was a glorious life of a
revolutionary. He had firmly struggled for and made indelible
historical contributions to the liberation of the Chinese people
and the founding of the new China, the cause of socialist
revolution and construction and the ultimate realization of
communism.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Peng Zhen plunged himself into the anti-imperialist,
anti-feudal struggle as a young man. He joined the Socialist Youth
League of China in 1923, and joined CPC the same year, thus being
one of the founding members of the Communist Party organization in
Shanxi Province. Between 1924 and 1929, he carried out
revolutionary activities in Taiyuan, Shijiazhuang, Tianjin and
Tangshan cities, serving as secretary of CPC Taiyuan branch,
secretary of the Taiyuan Area Committee of the Communist Youth
League of China, secretary of the Federation of Trade Unions of
Zhen-Tai Railway, director of the Organization Department of CPC
Tianjin Area Committee, secretary of Tianjin city CPC Committee,
director of the Organization Department and acting secretary of
the Shunzhi Provincial CPC Committee. As one of major CPC leaders
in northern China, he led the workers' and students' movements
there.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
