<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen Passes Away(3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He was sold out by traitors and arrested in Tianjin in 1929. He
set up a CPC branch in prison to carry on struggle there. In 1935,
after completing his sentence, he worked as representative of CPC
Central Committee's North China Bureau and director of its
Organization Department; he supported the basic principles and
tactics put forward by Comrade Liu Shaoqi regarding work in white
areas, thus playing an important role in reviving and developing
CPC organizations in northern China, consolidating and enhancing
achievements of "December 9" patriotic movement, promoting the
formation of the national united front against Japanese aggression
and opening up a new situation in the work in white areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
