<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Returns Home From Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Y. Museveni
returned home today from European tour during which he visited
the institutions of the European Union (EU) in Brussels and in
Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
He also held meetings with EU officials and was received by
the king of Belgium and the grand duke of Luxemburg as well as
other leaders in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In Belgium, the president gave a lecture on Uganda's
experience in governance and delivered a key note address at a
forum for investment and trade.
</P>
<P>
In Lexemburg among other engagements the president delivered
a key note address to African Caribbean Pacific/EU Council of
Ministers.
</P>
<P>
On his way home, he made a stop over in Cairo where he held
bilateral discussions with Egyptian PresidentHosni Mubarak.
</P>
</TEXT>
