<HEADLINE> Mubarak Arrive in S. Arabia to discuss Mideast peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
today arrived in the Saudi Arabian city of Jiddah to discuss the
deadlocked Middle East peace process, reports reaching here from
Jiddah said.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, Mubarak arrived in Saudi Arabia for a
24-hour visit beginning this evening, and he is scheduled to meet
with Saudi King Fahd on promotion of bilateral ties and on means
of getting the stalled peace process moving again.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak arrived in Jiddah from Kuwait, where he held talks
earlier today with Kuwaiti leaders on the stalemated peace process.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak, who visited Saudi Arabia last August, embarked on the
previously unannounced tour to discuss the peace process with the
leaders of oil-rich Gulf Arab states. He is expected to visit the
United Arab Emirates following the tour of Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
