<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Hails Jiang's Russia Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 26 (Xinhua) -- China's leading newspaper, the
People's Daily, publishes an editorial on Sunday, hailing Chinese
President Jiang Zemin's successful Russia tour as the one of great
significance and far-reaching impact.
</P>
<P>
The editorial, entitled "A Visit of Great Significance and
Far-Reaching Impact," said Jiang's April 22-26 Russia tour not
only opened a new chapter in the history of Sino-Russian
relations, but also was conducive to maintaining peace and
stability in the region and would push forward the trend of global
multipolarization and the establishment of a peaceful, stable,
just and equitable new international order.
</P>
<P>
"As the world situation develops, people will see more and more
clearly the great contribution President Jiang has made in his
visit and the significance of the tour," the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Jiang held his fourth summit with Russian
President Boris Yeltsin and signed a five-nation accord on mutual
reduction of military forces in the border areas with the
presidents of Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
"China and Russia are the biggest neighbors to each other.
Establishing and developing a strategic partnership and
maintaining long-term friendship and good neighborliness will
promote development and prosperity on both sides and serve the
well-being of the two peoples," the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
In Moscow, Jiang and Yeltsin announced the official
establishment of the Sino-Russian Friendship Committee for Peace
and Development, providing a new guarantee for passing the
Sino-Russian friendship from generation to generation, the
editorial said.
</P>
<P>
"Its implementation will prove that relations between the two
countries are full of vitality and will stand the test of time,"
it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
