<HEADLINE> Clinton Urges to Increase Literacy Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton is
calling for one million tutors with a goal of teaching children to
read by age eight.
</P>
<P>
In his weekly radio address Saturday, Clinton said he will send
legislation to Congress on Monday to fund the five-year, 2.75
billion-dollar America Reads Challenge.
</P>
<P>
The president said the legislation, part of his balanced budget
proposal, and will fund 25,000 reading specialists and tutor
coordinators, including 11,000 AmeriCorps members and many others.
</P>
<P>
He said, "They will recruit and train our America Reads citizen
army, bringing reading help to the 3 million children who need it
the most."  
</P>
</TEXT>
