<HEADLINE> French Humanitarian Group Urges Rescue of Rwandan Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The French humanitarian group
Medecins sans Frontieres (MSF) today called for "an immediate
action" to look for 85,000 Rwandan Hutu refugees reportedly
missing in eastern Zaire.
</P>
<P>
In a communique issued in Paris today, the MSF also urged the
Zairian rebel forces of Laurent-Desire Kabila to cease immediately
"to proceed the elimination of these refugees," and help
humanitarian workers look for, gather and save them.
</P>
<P>
It said that it has failed to obtain any information on the
whereabout of these refugees, who diappeared from the Kasese and
Biaro refugee camps south of Kisangani.
</P>
<P>
The MSF also called on the United Nations High Commission for
Refugees to abandon its plan to repatriate these refugees back to
Rwanda, and instead evacuate them to a third country other than
Zaire or Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
"These refugees should be received provisionally in a country
of the region, other than Zaire and Rwanda, where their security
can be guaranteed," said the MSF.
</P>
<P>
The MSF Friday accused the Zairian rebels of following a
strategy of "physical elimination" of the refugees in eastern
Zaire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
