<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Killed in California House Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- 10 people, including five
children, were killed in an early morning house fire in east Palo
Alto, California, about 40 miles south of San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
A Menlo Park Fire Department spokesman said firefighters were
called to the residence and the blaze was quickly extinguished
after firefighters worked their way around numerous obstacles,
according to news reports.
</P>
<P>
Neighbors told reporters that the home most likely did not have
a safety release mechanism inside for the barred windows because
such mechanisms apparently aren't available in most of their
homes.
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said it appears the victims were members of the
same family. An investigation into the cause of the blaze is
underway.  
</P>
</TEXT>
