<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen Passes Away (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After the outbreak of the War of Resistance against Japanese
Aggression, Comrade Peng Zhen participated in planning the Party's
work in waging a guerrilla warfare in the northern area and
establishing base areas for resisting Japanese aggression. In
1938, he served as secretary of the CPC Central Committee's
Shanxi-Chahar-Hebei Sub-bureau and set up the Shanxi-Chahar-Hebei
Anti-Japanese Base Area together with Nie Rongzhen and other
comrades. He creatively carried out the strategic principles and
the basic policy of the CPC Central Committee on the Anti-Japanese
War, mobilized the masses, and expanded people's forces. The
Shaxi-Chahar-Hebei border area was praised by the Party Central
Committee as a "Model Anti-Japanese Base Area behind the enemy
lines and a Model Area of the united front work."
</P>
<P>
In 1941 when he was in Yan'an, he served as dean of education
and vice-president of the Party School of the CPC Central
Committee, head of the Organization Department and head of the
Urban Work Department of the CPC Central Committee. He joined the
leadership of the rectification movement in Yan'an, making major
contributions to summing up the party's historical experience,
unifying the Party's thinking to the correct line headed by
Comrade Mao Zedong, establishing the leading position of Mao
Zedong Thought in the Party, training leaders of the Party, and
launching underground work in the enemy-occupied areas and
Kuomintang-occupied areas.
</P>
<P>
He was elected member of the CPC Central Committee and member
of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee at the
Seventh Party Congress and the first plenary session of the
Seventh Party Central Committee held in 1945. In August 1945, he
was added to the secretariate of the CPC Central Committee as an
alternate member.
</P>
<P>
After the victory of the Anti-Japanese War, Comrade Peng Zhen,
working for implementing the strategic policy-decision of winning
over northeast China made at the Seventh Party Congress, held the
post of secretary of Northeast China Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee and Political Commissar of the Northeast Democratic
Allied Forces, earnestly implemented the decisions, instructions
and orders of the CPC Central Committee, the Central Military
Commission and Chairman Mao Zedong in complicated and capricious
situation, smashed the military offensives of the Kuomintang
reactionaries, fully aroused the masses, enlarged the people's
forces, rapidly expanded the troops and established revolutionary
bases, thus paving the way for future greater victory.
</P>
<P>
In 1947, he returned to the Central Committee and held the post
of standing committee member of the working Committee of the CPC
Central Committee, head of the Organization Department and
director of the policy research office.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
