<DOCNO> XIE19970427.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen Passes Away (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During the "Cultural Revolution," Comrade Peng Zhen was wrongly
repudiated and cruelly persecuted by Lin Biao, Jiang Qing and
their like, and was stripped of all posts in and outside the Party
and lost his personal freedom. He waged a firm struggle against
Lin Biao, Jiang Qing and their like. After the Third Plenum of the
Eleventh Party Central Committee, the Central Committee declared
that "all the charges, slanders and libels imposed on Comrade Peng
Zhen" during the "Cultural Revolution" "should be repudiated."
</P>
<P>
After Comrade Peng Zhen resumed his work, he was by-elected as
member of the CPC Central Committee and member of the Committee's
Political Bureau at the Fourth Plenum of the 11th Party Central
Committee held in September 1979, and afterwards re-elected as
member of the 12th Party Central Committee and member of its
Political Bureau. In 1980, he became secretary of the Political
and Law Commission of the Party Central Committee. At the Second
Session of the Fifth National People's Congress (NPC) held in June
1979, he was by-elected as vice-chairman of the NPC Standing
Committee and became director of the Commission of Legislative
Affairs of the Standing Committee. At the First Session of the
Sixth NPC held in June 1983, he was elected chairman of the NPC
Standing Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
