<DOCNO> XIE19970427.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen Passes Away (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During the new historical period, Comrade Peng Zhen, as a
principal member of the leadership team of the Party and state
with Comrade Deng Xiaoping at the core, took part in formulating a
series of major policies of the Party and state, making important
contributions to the work of bringing order out of chaos, defining
and implementing the Party'sbasic line of taking economic
construction as the central task while adhering to the four
cardinal principles and persevering in reform and opening-up
drive, and building socialism with Chinese characteristics, and to
the reunification of the motherland and the unity of all ethnic
groups. Since he presided over the NPC Standing Committee's work
for a long period and also took charge of the job of the politics
and law front, he had made outstanding contributions to
establishing and perfecting the system of the people's congresses,
strengthening and consolidating the political power of people's
democratic dictatorship, developing socialist democracy, and
improving the socialist legal system. In 1980, he served as
vice-chairman of the constitutional revision committee to directly
preside over the work of revising China's Constitution. Since
1979, he had directed the job of formulating a number of basic and
important laws, thus laying a solid foundation for China's
socialist legal system.
</P>
<P>
Since retiring from leading positions in 1988, Comrade Peng
Zhen had still been concerned about China's reform and opening-up
program and socialist modernization drive, resolutely supported
the central collective leadership with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the
core, highly appraised the important speeches Comrade Deng
Xiaoping made during his tour of south China in 1992 and the
guidelines of a plenary meeting of the Political Bureau of the
Party Central Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
