<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Communist Party Calls for Real Leftist Alternative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The national secretary of the
French Communist Party (PCF) Robert Hue today called for the
presentation of a real leftist alternative by the Socialist Party
and its leftist allies in the coming legislative elections.
</P>
<P>
In his first public appearance of legislative campaign in
Argenteuil, northwest of Paris, Hue told about 300 supporters that
an alternative project by the leftist parties should be, "without
ambiguity, a real project of the left."
</P>
<P>
"What do we propose to (Prime Minister) Juppe? Restriction, a
smoked herring," he said in response to a statement by Juppe made
on Thursday in Marseille that the Socialist Party and the
Communist Party can only serve a plate of small beans to the
French.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the first secretary of the Socialist Party Lionel
Jospin today hinted that if his party wins the legislative
elections, it could take in PCF members into a new government.
</P>
<P>
"What is the problem? It was possible in 1945 with General de
Gaulle and in 1981 with Francois Mitterrand," said Jospin in a
television interview.
</P>
<P>
PCF members served as government ministers under President
Charles de Gaulled after World War II and under President Francois
Mitterrand in the early 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Hue and Jospin will meet on Tuesday next week to discuss a
common line by their two parties in the general elections
scheduled for May 25 and June 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
