<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen Passes Away (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said that Comrade Deng Xiaoping had said that adherence to
"one central task and two basic points" (taking economic
development as the central task and upholding reform and
opening-up policy and the four cardinal principles) is the basic
line of the CPC. The Party should concentrate on securing a faster
and better economic development, give full play to the fine
tradition of the CPC, and pay equal attention to the development
of both material and ideological progress. Since reform and
opening to the outside world is to emancipate and promote
productive forces, so China should stick to them until the
realization of communism.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Peng Zhen firmly supported and upheld the principles
and policies adopted since the 14th National Congress of the CPC
Central Committee, and highly praised the achievements that the
Party has made since its 14th National Congress.
</P>
<P>
During his 70-odd years of revolutionary career, Comrade Peng
Zhen had firm belief in communism, showed utmost loyalty to the
Party, the people and the cause of proletarian revolution, and
kept fighting indomitably in spite of twists and turns.
</P>
</TEXT>
