<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen Passes Away (9) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He deligently studied Marxism, persisted in combining theory
with practice and was good at applying Marxist stand, viewpoint
and method. He was quick to discover problems, analysed and solved
them in a realistic way, displaying the courage and organizational
talent of a revolutionary in creatively opening up a new situation
and handling complicated problems.
</P>
<P>
He had always adhered to the principles at the crucial
junctures and on the major issues which had an important bearing
on the future and the destiny of the Party and the state.
</P>
<P>
He steadfastly kept to the (Party's) aim of serving the people
wholeheartedly, acted in the best interests of the overwhelming
majority of people and maintained the true qualities of a public
servant of the people.
</P>
<P>
He stuck to the principle of democratic centralism and Party's
collective leadership and to the mass line, went deep into the
realities of life, made investigations and study, was democratic
in his work style, paid attention to different opinions, pooled
the wisdom of the masses and was resourceful and resolute in
making decisions.
</P>
<P>
He was modest and prudent, simple and unadorned, strict with
himself, upheld the truth and was ready at any time to correct
mistakes.
</P>
</TEXT>
