<DOCNO> XIE19970427.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen Passes Away (10) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He had largeness of mind, open and above-board, took the
interests of the whole into account and played an exemplary role
in observing the party's discipline. He showed great care to his
comrades, loved cadres, respected knowledge and talents and
trained a great number of leading officials for the Party's
cause. Comrade Peng Zhen was worthy of being a proletarian
revolutionary of the older generation with noble character and
enjoying high prestige, who had made outstanding deeds of merit
and was deeply loved by the whole Party and people of all ethnic
groups.
</P>
<P>
The death of Comrade Peng Zhen was a great loss for the Party
and the state. The whole Party and people of all ethnic groups in
China should turn grief into strength, conscientiously learn the
revolutionary spirit and noble character of Comrade Peng Zhen,
closely rally around the Party Central Committee with Comrade
Jiang Zemin as the core and strive tirelessly for the building of
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Eternal glory to the great proletarian revolutionary and
statesman Comrade Peng Zhen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
