<HEADLINE> Greece Intensifies Patrols After Officer's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Greece ordered today increased
patrols along the coast of Corfu facing Albania following a Greek
coastguard officer was killed by unidentified gunmen off the
island.
</P>
<P>
According to the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) today,
the order was given by Greece's Minister of Merchant Marine
Stavros Soumakis.
</P>
<P>
Greek police said that the officer, 22, was shot on the head
and died on the spot when his patrol boat came under fire from the
gunmen, believed to be Albanians, on a speedboat off the island
of Corfu.
</P>
<P>
The Greek coastguard officers returned the fire, and according
to the police, at least three of the speedboat passengers were
hit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
